#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:1
#: 47e0552ea5f741fd9a0d5e762caa576a
msgid "Software that is too complicated to use, is often unused. Because we want as many people as possible to benefit from its unique security properties, the usability and user experience of Qubes OS is an utmost priority!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:6
#: cd1870a6193b4e4288385bb0fa8d4430
msgid "We ask anyone developing for Qubes OS to please read through this guide to better understand the user experience we strive to achieve. We also ask them to review :doc:`our visual style guide </developer/general/visual-style-guide>` for other design related information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:14
#: 388241643df84d908fbe8feaf3c7a573
msgid "Easy To Use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:16
#: d80390288bfd45468f04d1a9dafc3e2e
msgid "An ideal user experience is friendly, and it beckons a new user to explore the interface. In this process, they can naturally discover how to use the software. Below are some guidelines that will help you design a user interface that accomplishes this goal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:23
#: c80a942c2a124ada8b85aee98c295b50
msgid "Interfaces Should Not"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:25
#: c19f326ad724487c9d4170c93d89fa61
msgid "Require extensive configuration before a user can *begin* doing things"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:27
#: f42c1af1c5634e789445b7c480fc0345
msgid "Make it possible to break provided features or actions in unrecoverable ways"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:29
#: 76c2a7758edb47db8cbf64a04b0f29ee
msgid "Perform actions which compromise security and data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:30
#: e79e34814aa5457dbe69348275da5b72
msgid "Overwhelm the user with too much information and cognitive load"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:32
#: 5d3c1e62587f4475a61426fcc4f8d460
msgid "Perhaps the most common cause of mistakes is complexity. If there is a configuration setting that will significantly affect the user’s experience, choose a safe and smart default then tuck this setting in an ``Advanced Settings`` panel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:39
#: 7f0a9b22444d42d69cd084f623ea9b5e
msgid "Interfaces Should"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:41
#: ed672079dec0433b8d0f3836449252a4
msgid "Make it easy to discover features and available actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:42
#: 5ab00d5673b8426ca2fda164ccec6aed
msgid "Provide some understanding of what discovered features do"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:43
#: fe41dcdaa4c14db9aaacc79b1ea4bf44
msgid "Offer the ability to easily undo mistakes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:44
#: 6cef4b14e02d458889c820763d8fcbb8
msgid "Choose intelligent defaults for settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:46
#: 3f87549385e347609ebb8f9353cc69ef
msgid "In making software easy to use, it is crucial to be mindful of `cognitive load <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognitive_load>`__ which dictates that *“humans are generally able to hold only seven +/- two units of information in short-term memory.”* Making sure your interfaces don’t pass this short-term memory limit is perhaps the most important factor in helping a user feel comfortable instead of overwhelmed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:56
#: cad76b548aff43b6bf3fe532ed621d56
msgid "Easy to Understand"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:58
#: 8c18877065194f6e9905303603292e6e
msgid "There will always be the need to communicate things to users. In these cases, an interface should aim to make this information easy to understand. The following are simple guides to help achieve this - none of these are absolute maxims!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:65
#: 50fddaa8a8f94930a95fb7a67761ba43
msgid "Avoid Acronyms"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:67
#: 917c11040b0b452b806f39fd0f8703e2
msgid "Acronyms are compact and make good names for command line tools. They do not make graphical user interfaces more intuitive for non-technical users. Until one learns an acronym’s meaning, it is gibberish. Avoid acronyms in your interfaces whenever possible!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:72
#: 0a5fa79d21a044e09cdff1a9e920b651
msgid "``DVM`` - Disposable Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:73
#: 10f1a988dfca49f89506b781758cd374
msgid "``GUID`` - Global Unique Identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:74
#: 943cb87e46664d1b8eac52fe6a046208
msgid "``PID`` - Process Identification Number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:75
#: 2013f90320cf42acb5e908e51d96deec
msgid "``NetVM`` - Networking Virtual Machine"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:77
#: 5fe83d86dae547be8aff9ea9b2819637
msgid "Despite this rule, some acronyms like ``USB`` are widely used and understood due to being in common use for over a decade. It is good to use these acronyms when the full words like ``Universal Serial Bus`` are more likely to confuse users."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:84
#: 15289bbab3734e1ab0384eef8f4d8ec1
msgid "Use Simple Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:86
#: 3e9cb00a7f5a421383fc21763d204ceb
msgid "Use the minimum amount of words needed to be descriptive, but also informative. Go with common words that are as widely understood. Sometimes, inventing a word such as ``Qube`` to describe a ``virtual machine`` makes the life of the user much easier."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:91
#: 5c9bb1b1919b4834a812d2f050cf6c2b
msgid "Use ``Disposable Qube`` instead of ``DVM`` or ``Disposable Virtual Machine``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:93
#: 0512e69d7ead415696a6f312f91b4d77
msgid "Use ``interface`` instead of ``GUI`` or ``Graphical User Interface``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:94
#: b706cd04246e4c079a9e7274695ab051
msgid "Use ``application number`` instead of ``PID`` or ``Process Identification Number``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:96
#: b17028756f7149239083ca976aea5e31
msgid "Use ``Networking`` or ``Networking Qube`` instead of ``NetVM`` given context"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:103
#: 81671c8541b14baa872b066a0aad913a
msgid "Avoid Technical Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:105
#: 8ad99051a77f4e92a8e43382da3c2bb2
msgid "Technical words are usually more accurate, but they often *only* make sense to technical users and are confusing and unhelpful to non-technical users. Examples of technical words that might show up in Qubes OS are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:110
#: 112e015526c64f019e52fe22e5e93e46
msgid "``root.img``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:111
#: 148d7bc600a24d91ae2fc86fd094cd66
msgid "``savefile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:112
#: 7317d88e56b34f9cbfff4c9a532d4631
msgid "``qrexec-daemon``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:114
#: 65d31a7163094c929a45dd15bc81c4c5
msgid "These are all terms that have at some point showed up in users’ notification messages. Each term is very specific, but requires the user to understand virtualization to interpret."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:120
#: 1d01ecfe48f54f9bb9b34acdb5c9d48a
msgid "Use Common Concepts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:122
#: 390a078bf2854aca89425a6ee90e5d65
msgid "Large amounts of the global population have been using computers for one or two decades and have formed some mental models of how things work. Leveraging these mental models are a huge gain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:126
#: f336bb17b328404a9ac4b51f4dacb79f
msgid "Use ``disk space`` instead of ``root.img``, since while not quite accurate, it makes contextual sense"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:128
#: 02cf1d1dd5c74c26a742e6eba1dd2675
msgid "Use ``saving`` instead of ``savefile`` as the former is the action trying to be completed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:130
#: fcfca3764a7849bb89c61956aeb68d51
msgid "Use ``Qubes`` instead of ``qrexec-daemon`` as it gives better context on what is happening"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:133
#: 3b009dbf06b841ca9ce9eaaca0662b68
msgid "These words are more abstract and user relevant- they help a user understand what is happening based on already known concepts (disk space) or start to form a mental model of something new (Qubes)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:141
#: c2e5588f9f494283b7fb2fcb5218835e
msgid "Avoid Inconsistencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:143
#: 5751858c492448ce927f90c652cc7ddb
msgid "It is easy to start abbreviating (or making acronyms) of long terms like ``Disposable Virtual Machine`` depending on where the term shows up in an interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:147
#: ad8b3d05c705408e8360f815171e16ab
msgid "``DVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:148
#: 7cc469fdd4ea43aba4e55b5e3fd9bc99
msgid "``DispVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:149
#: 428ee57ce6f3411093b502f2e211f7d9
msgid "``DisposableVM``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:151
#: 4afdd62ab9da4c56bfc19e9282b3dfa7
msgid "This variation in terms can cause new users to question or second guess what the three different variations mean, which can lead to inaction or mistakes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:157
#: c3d3f9acef514419828b6618b565bdae
msgid "Make Things Consistent"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:159
#: f2d0add86e284f459f9458387c9b7250
msgid "Always strive to keep things consistent in the interfaces as well as documentation and other materials."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:162
#: 56f9d265248b42099751a1d0f99a1a81
msgid "Use ``Disposable Qube`` at all times as it meets other criteria as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:165
#: 5d02d5df810b487b99058c12b2b4bc29
msgid "By using the same term throughout an interface, a user can create a mental model and relationship with that term allowing them to feel empowered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:173
#: 1930893da41e40819f0921df12230f75
msgid "Avoid Duplicate Words"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:175
#: 563513c4e05243a28bdfc2e3217d7b62
msgid "It is easy to add words like ``Domain`` before items in a list or menu in an attempt to be descriptive, such as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:185
#: 5437533104834a1f982ee7d9c139d9df
msgid "The repeated use of the word ``Domain`` requires a user to read it for each item in the list, which makes extra work for the eye in parsing out the relevant word like ``work, banking, or personal``. This also affects horizontal space on fixed width lines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:192
#: 66c7aacec91348fa82db7414b8bbd218
msgid "Create Groups & Categories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:194
#: f898443a3610418ba6b38f5417416743
msgid "It is more efficient to group things under headings instead as this allows the eye to easily scan the uniqueness of the items. (As per our previous example:)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:208
#: cf4a26548bcf474da02db84163af2714
msgid "Easy To Complete"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:210
#: b6d9948cf11c4b13ac60a68f7fa5fb70
msgid "Lastly, expected (and unexpected) situations often require user actions or input. Make resolving these occurences as easy as possible to complete the action."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:216
#: 0990bf03690749f7b50754c609b437b8
msgid "Don’t Leave Users Stranded"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:218
#: 8e869b44c10d4d0da1e5b4c081d7fb31
msgid "Consider the following notifications:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:220
#: fef0a89bbc6443549f7df6a28f72d337
msgid "``The disk space of your Qube \"Work\" is full``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:221
#: b16d103c56bc4e83aee81f8e6d909945
msgid "``There was an error saving Qube \"Personal\"``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:223
#: 38878fcd10a045f9901058942ea500df
msgid "Instead of displaying solvable errors like these and neglecting to provide a fix:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:228
#: 161eb1c69e59404f9cdde05891989bd1
msgid "Offer Actionable Solutions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:230
#: aaec8f0e413f431b81bb56ad3dcf3a61
msgid "Error messages and limits such as those in the previous example can be greatly improved by adding buttons or links to helpful information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:233
#: c2efeb39033d427bbc49098ceb4e5536
msgid "Add a button to ``Increase Disk Space``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:234
#: 681100266ab34af5a4f69d4682554b42
msgid "Add a link to a documentation page called ``Troubleshoot saving data``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../_doc/developer/general/usability-ux.rst:237
#: d7d7cbc5f90c4fd182aecc5a7adb4f73
msgid "In adhering to these principles, you’ll make undesirable situations more manageable for users instead of feeling stranded."
msgstr ""

